WEBVTT

00:04:28.158 --> 00:04:30.181
It will recognize

00:04:30.866 --> 00:04:33.801
that the keywords "Mozart,"
"last" and "symphony"

00:04:33.825 --> 00:04:36.728
are appearing heavily around here.

00:04:37.790 --> 00:04:42.165
So if it can find a word which is a planet

00:04:42.189 --> 00:04:45.837
and which is co-occurring
with these keywords,

00:04:45.861 --> 00:04:47.850
that must be the answer.

00:04:48.762 --> 00:04:53.948
This is how Watson finds
the answer "Jupiter," in this case.

00:04:56.433 --> 00:05:00.482
Our Todai Robot works similarly,
but a bit smarter